"digit indicates whether it contains numbers, and symbol indicates whether it contains special symbols.\n"
"exclude_symbols is used to exclude specific symbols. You can fill in the symbol characters to be excluded (up to 16). \n"
"If you do not need to exclude symbols, you can leave it blank.\n"
"default: {\"length\": 16, \"lowercase\": true, \"uppercase\": true, \"digit\": true, \"symbol\": true, \"exclude_symbols\": \"\"}"
msgstr ""
"length is the password length, ranging from 8 to 30. lowercase indicates "
"whether the password contains lowercase letters, uppercase indicates whether"
" it contains uppercase letters, digit indicates whether it contains numbers,"
" and symbol indicates whether it contains special symbols. exclude_symbols "
"is used to exclude specific symbols; you can fill in the symbols you want to"
" exclude (up to 16). If no symbols need to be excluded, you can leave it "
"blank. Default: {\"length\": 16, \"lowercase\": true, \"uppercase\": true, "
"\"digit\": true, \"symbol\": true, \"exclude_symbols\": \"\"}"

